    id: 'ab1c50d9-9258-4eba-b3da-321f6ebe4188',
    answer:
      '<p><br></p><p>That‚Äôs a very good question. If you  want to target the best online products audience in facebook ads, you have to take note of these two things; your ad copy and your target audience. If you don‚Äôt get them right you will waste your time, money and energy. What is an ad copy and how does it affect my sales?</p><p><br></p><p><strong>1)Ad copy</strong></p><p>An ad copy is the content of your advert. There are certain guidelines and principles you need to follow in creating an ad copy. Once you follow them, it becomes a walk in the park. Here are the most important guidelines you need to follow. There are 9 of them. You can call them the 9 COMMANDMENTS in facebook ads marketing.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>#1. Your ad copy must arrest attention; </strong>This is the most important commandment of creating an ad copy. The reason is because if your advert doesn‚Äôt attract attention no one would notice it. For facebook ads, the best way to arrest attention is to have a powerful headline and a nice clear portrait picture. Don‚Äôt try to be creative and leave the juice to the end. Do something from the first second. For example; you want to run an advert for your new product (hair cream) for those who fancy having a dark hair. Why not have a headline like this ‚ÄúGet a dark hair in one week‚Äù than ‚Äú Buy our (product name) to get a dark hair‚Äù.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>#2.your ad copy must contain an offer</strong>; Nigerians like freebies. They always want something to ginger them to act. Imagine you see two adverts on facebook from different company offering the same services. Let‚Äôs say an insurance company,</p><p>Advert 1 says</p><p>&nbsp;‚ÄúInnosuccess insurance.&nbsp;In these turbulent times, you need an insurance partner to count on. Solid, caring and reliable.‚Äù</p><p>Advert 2 says</p><p>‚Äú Mr Kings vehicle insurance. Insure your car and get 50% off your renewal.‚Äù</p><p>Which of the advert above will catch your attention? It is obvious that the second advert has an offer.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>#3. Your ad copy should have a call to action ‚ÄúCTA‚Äù;</strong>I mentioned earlier an offer will make your prospects respond to your offer but you have to tell them to do it. It has to be something like;</p><p>For free consultation, send an email to‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..</p><p>&nbsp;For free access to our articles and interactive session, visit‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.</p><p>To read the rest, click‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..</p><p>To place an order, call 090XXXXX</p><p><strong>#4. Your ad copy must create a sense of urgency;</strong>One thing you must know for sure is that 21st century buyers are lazy and busy. I‚Äôm also guilty of that, I will be like I will check later, I will order later, I will make enquiries later. It is always later. This is why your ad copy should create a sense of urgency. For example, don‚Äôt&nbsp;mind me I like giving examples for better understanding. Assuming you want to run ads for your new boutique. Your ad copy should have something like;</p><p>‚ÄúJames boutique. Get 50% discount when you visit our boutique for the first time. Offer valid for&nbsp;50 customers. Call 090xxx to book your slot‚Äù.</p><p><strong>#5. You must test; </strong>My students hate me for this because whenever I give them assignments to create an ad copy, I will tell them to create 5 each. If you don‚Äôt like wasting money, oops too bad. This commandment is a must follow for you. It helps in getting the most results from your advertising efforts. You have to produce 2-5 ad copies to see which ads converts faster. That way, you will put most of your advertising budget into what works.</p><p>Note; your opinion doesn‚Äôt count. Let me repeat YOUR OPINION IS USELESS, IT DOESN‚ÄôT COUNT. Don‚Äôt think because a particular ad copy looks attractive to you means it will convert faster. For example,&nbsp;you run&nbsp;ads for your online course and you have something like these on your 3 different adverts;</p><p>1.Bring a friend and get&nbsp;free voucher for our premium course</p><p>2. If our course is not educative, don‚Äôt pay for it</p><p>3. Pay for a course and get one free</p><p>You might be thinking no.3 would bring more people in. Don‚Äôt be surprised that no.2 out performs the others. Concentrate on the ad copy that brings more customers. That is smart marketing.</p><p><strong>#6.you must establish credibility</strong>; why should they trust you? Why should they believe you ? Why should they patronize you? You are nobody. You have to establish credibility by:</p><p>Get some people to use your products and give testimony. Share their testimony</p><p>Get an expert endorse your product for you.</p><p>If you are using a website; you can have options like good looking interface, easy web navigation etc</p><p><strong>#7. Your ad copy should take the risk away from their potential customers; </strong>every buying decision is like a gamble. If you are buying something online, you are scared of not getting the product the way you saw them on net. So how can you take the risk way from potential customers? You can do that by; offering a money back guarantee, service change guarantee, product change guarantee etc.</p><p><strong>#8. Use the right words</strong>; facebook ban ads that contain offensive or harsh words. Words that make the customers feel bad about themselves. If you want to run an ad for a product that cures cancer, your ads shouldn‚Äôt&nbsp;start with ‚Äú If you don‚Äôt want cancer to kill you, buy this ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.‚Äù. The word ‚ÄúKill‚Äù would make your customers feel bad because you just remind them&nbsp;of their greatest fear. It should be‚Äù get rid of cancer‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.‚Äù</p><p><strong>#9. Take the bull by the horn; </strong>Its not an English class or a project where&nbsp;you will make your ad copy long and ambiguous. Make your sentence simple, apt and attractive. Facebook has limits of words for writing an ad copy besides people are lazy and busy. Nobody has time to read your long ad copy. It should not be too long nor too short. You can make it 50-&nbsp;150 words.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>2). Define your target audience</strong></p><p>People often make this mistake when running&nbsp;ads on facebook. They will select all demographics without selecting their specific target audience. Maybe because they want to reach a larger audience. It is better to reach 50k audience with 45k respondents than to reach 300k with 10k response. It saves cost. Defining your audience makes it easier for your ads to reach&nbsp;potential customers . I don‚Äôt expect you running an advert for a RELATIONSHIP class and you include (2-10 yrs of age) in your demographics. They are many free mode users that like clicking ads to waste your budget. Take note.</p><p><br></p><p>&nbsp;I hope&nbsp;I have answered your question. Thanks for reading. If you have more questions , your are free to ask. We are here at your service.</p>',
